25/07/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government approved on Thursday (24 July) two co-operation programmes with Turkey and the Spanish region of Catalonia. 
The joint programme with Turkey provides for co-operation in science, education and culture during the period 2003-2005. 
Under the agreement, the two countries will offer scholarships for scientific research, and will organise summer seminars on each other's language and culture. 
The second co-operation protocol, between Bulgaria and the autonomous government of Catalonia, envisions co-operation in the field of environmental protection. 
Valid for one year, it may be extended. 
(BTA, BNT - 24/07/03)
